<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6656> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6656" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried a plebiscite defining the attendants of the Pr. Urbanus (Censor. DN 24.3; cf. Plaut. Epid. 25-27; Varro LL 6.5; Gell. 3.2.4). Weiss (RE, s. v. \"Lex Plaetoria,\" no. 1) dates it before 241. Perhaps it was occasioned by the institution of the Pr. Peregrinus (Niccolini, FTP 396; Bruns, FIR7 45)." .
